paragraphs:
[6]
The part of the
Act
which applies to this dispute is s. 5:
"5(1) The Minister shall grant citizenship to any person who
(a) makes application for citizenship;
(b) is eighteen years of age or over;
(c) has been lawfully admitted to Canada for permanent residence, has not ceased since such admission to be a permanent resident pursuant to section 24 of the Immigration Act, and has, within the four years immediately preceding the date of his application, accumulated at least three years of residence in Canada calculated in the following manner:
(i) for every day during which the person was resident in Canada before his lawful admission to Canada for permanent residence the person shall be deemed to have accumulated one-half of a day of residence, and
(ii) for every day during which the person was resident in Canada after his lawful admission to Canada for permanent residence the person shall be deemed to have accumulated one day of residence;
(d) has an adequate knowledge of one of the official languages of Canada;
(e) has an adequate knowledge of Canada and of the responsibilities and privileges of citizenship; and
(f) is not under a deportation order and is not the subject of a declaration by the Governor-in-Council made pursuant to section 20."
"5(1) The Minister grants citizenship to any person who:
(a) requests it;
(b) is at least eighteen years old;
(c) was lawfully admitted to Canada as a permanent resident, has not since lost that title under section 24 of the Immigration Act, and has, in the four years preceding the date of his application, resided in Canada for at least three years in total, the duration of his residence being calculated as follows:
(i) half a day for each day of residence in Canada before admission as a permanent resident,
(ii) one day for each day of residence in Canada after admission as a permanent resident;
(d) has sufficient knowledge of one of the official languages of Canada;
(e) has sufficient knowledge of Canada and the responsibilities and benefits conferred by citizenship;
(f) is not subject to a deportation order and is not the subject of a declaration of the Governor in Council made under section 20."
